Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setProbePin(25.10)                                          setProbePin(25.10)

Name
       setProbePin - Sets a pad or bump as a probe point

Syntax
       setProbePin

       [-help]

       {{-instName <instName> -pinName <pinName>}

        | -bump <bumpName>}}

       Sets a pad or bump as a probe point. Probe points are used for package-
       level  design and testing. To delete or report on probe points, use the
       unsetProbePin or reportProbePins commands respectively.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each setProbePin parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man setProbePin

       -bump <bumpName>
              Specifies the instance name of the bump.

       -instName <InstName>
              Specifies the name of the I/O instance.

       -pinName <pinName>
              Specifies  the  name of the pin on the I/O instance that will be
              set as a probe point.

Example
              * The following command sets pin PAD of I/O instance Bump_1 as a
                probe point:

                setProbePin -instName Bump_1 -pinName PAD

Related Information
              * reportProbePins

              * unsetProbePin

